      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;If you enable navigation (on by default), the app starts with the first page in your navigation.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1731252322568.png" style="width: 839px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/188850i54E8B80D1AA2E2D1/image-dimensions/839x407?v=v2" width="839" height="407" role="button" title="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1731252322568.png" alt="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1731252322568.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;If you disable navigation, there is a setting to specify which page to start on.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="Dan_Wroblewski_1-1731252365432.png" style="width: 971px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/188851iB27D7C1D784C02E9/image-dimensions/971x472?v=v2" width="971" height="472" role="button" title="Dan_Wroblewski_1-1731252365432.png" alt="Dan_Wroblewski_1-1731252365432.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;You could use the page mounted event on your first page and redirect to any other page, in the case where you want lets say page 3 to be the first page in the menu but then bring users to the Home Page to start. Not sure it wouldn't be better to create your own navigation menu.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/re-how-to-manage-startup-page-in-sap-build-app/qaq-p/13933433/comment-id/4891791#M4891791"/>
    <published>2024-11-10T16:29:04.581000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
  <entry>
    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/sap-builders-discussions/sap-bpa-environment-variables/m-p/13933443#M2604</id>
    <title>Re: SAP BPA - Environment Variables</title>
    <updated>2024-11-10T16:38:10.499000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Dan_Wroblewski</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;The values of environment variables are set when you deploy the process, so I don;t think that would meet your needs.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Off the top of my head, you could create a decision in a separate project, and then create a dependency to the decision in your project to take the output of the decision. Everytime you want to change the user you would just need to update the decision project. See this Devtoberfest session where they talk about making decisions as dependencies: &lt;A href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ajbnWJvVNuQ" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer"&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ajbnWJvVNuQ&lt;/A&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Not sure this is the best, since you still have to deploy the decision each time, but that is simpler than the entire project.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;If this isn't clear let me know. I also see if there is a better way.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/sap-builders-discussions/sap-bpa-environment-variables/m-p/13933443#M2604"/>
    <published>2024-11-10T16:38:10.499000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
  <entry>
    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/sap-builders-discussions/sap-bpa-environment-variables/m-p/13934313#M2606</id>
    <title>Re: SAP BPA - Environment Variables</title>
    <updated>2024-11-11T16:01:45.506000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Dan_Wroblewski</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;A simpler way to do it would be to create a group in the Custom IDP with any users who can approve, and specify this group as the approvers. Whenever you want to change the users you just change the users in the group.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/sap-builders-discussions/sap-bpa-environment-variables/m-p/13934313#M2606"/>
    <published>2024-11-11T16:01:45.506000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
